SOUL OF AN ANGEL raced off the pace three wide early, angled in nearing the far turn and lacked the needed rally. MIDNIGHT STROLL raced off the early pace three wide, advanced four wide around the far turn and came up empty in the lane. JUNGLE JUICE (IRE) bobbled at the break, set the pace inside and faltered midway around the far turn.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUST A CARE (IRE) chased in the four path, ranged up in the five path around the turn and was cued right handed in the six path at the top of the lane, and rallied to draw past an inner foe in the final sixteenth. CALABRIAN QUEEN set the pace while shifting inside into the turn, was roused in the two path passing the quarter pole and cued right handed at the top of the lane, ran on but was caught by an outer foe in the final sixteenth to place. GOLDEN STAR raced prominently along the inside, was roused to bid between rivals from the four path around the turn and urged right handed into the lane, and kept on to hold show. ASTRILA had to steady early, rated in the two path, advanced around the turn was driven into the stretch, but evened out passing the eighth pole. MISS UPROAR tracked in the three path, had to steady slightly early around the turn to avoid a fading foe, floated out to the seven path into the stretch, but was no factor. CORA'S CHOICE raced wellback along the inside, was urged into the lane, and flattened passing the eighth pole. OLYMPIC ARTIST bumped with an inner foe at the start, raced off the pace in the four path and never threatened while going wide into the stretch. ALGARCA bumped with an outer foe at the start, trailed in the three path into the turn and was never a menace. FAMOSA prompted the pace in the three path, began to fade early around the turn, took an awkward step and was precautionarily pulled up nearing the quarter pole, and walked off.
